Twitter has officially apologised to users whose timelines update randomly. Early in the year, Twitter rolled out a new desktop design that added more customisation options and completely rearranged the navigation experience. But it came with a bug that constantly updates the timeline, regardless of what action the user is taking. Most desktop and iPhone users have been complaining about how the error updates the timeline as you scroll. But on Monday, the Twitter support team apologised fro the inconvenience. Others complained bitterly through their account saying;